7.4 The Parties mutually understand and consent that CERES shall make every reasonable effort to fulfill its reporting obligations to DEFRA as outlined in the DEFRA agreement NF 0426 (as detailed in EXHIBIT E), subject to the conditions that:

1. CERES will not disclose any IGER BACKGROUND INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY, IGER INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY, or other research results derived from its own RESEARCH PROJECTS;
2. To the extent permitted by applicable regulations, CERES will strive to preserve the confidentiality of all other research findings and results generated during the course of the RESEARCH PROJECTS;
3. Prior to submission, CERES will share a draft of any such reports with IGER at least thirty (30) days in advance for review, comments, or feedback, and will consider any input received from IGER in good faith.
